Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.52,0:00:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎收看 我是马克\N{\fs(20)}Reporters on France24. I am Mark Owen. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,本期节目我们关注中国异议人士失踪之谜\N{\fs(20)}In this edition the mystries of why those who expressed views different to those of the government disappeared in China
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,听多了关于中国经济 环境 文化扩张的报道\N{\fs(20)}We spent a lot of time as journalist reporting on the business environment and culture reach of China
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,本期节目将揭示和北京有不同意见的人士所面对的恐怖\N{\fs(20)}This program though will expose the horror of being a person who dares to disagree with Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,其在生理 心理 及经济上的残忍程度是我们很多人无法想象的\N{\fs(20)}You'll see it's of a cruelty many of us will find impossible to imagine physically psychologically financially too
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,人权卫士也可能包括马克龙总统\N{\fs(20)}Defenders of human rights politically speaking of being that including the French president Emmanuel Macron
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:01:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,交易完成了 异议人士的命运却还是个未知数\N{\fs(20)}Deals are done dissidents though and everyone else whose views and conduct may not be in step with the government suffer an unknown fate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,原则在利益面前往往落败\N{\fs(20)}When it comes to trade vs principles trade always wins
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.22,0:01:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,还有那些失踪者的家人们...\N{\fs(20)}What about the families of those who were still missing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.80,0:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们一起来看看两位记者Forget和Vedeilhe的报道\N{\fs(20)}as reports by Angelique Forget and Antoine Vedeilhe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.70,0:01:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,一位书商的遭遇震动了香港
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.66,0:01:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他被中国政府绑架
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,关押 审讯数月
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.02,0:01:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,仅仅因为店里出售批评北京方面的书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.48,0:01:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,书商失踪8个月后回家\N{\fs(20)}... bookseller to return home after been missing for eight months
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.56,0:01:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,本周早些时候（2016年6月14日） 林荣基\N{\fs(20)}Earlier this week Lam Wing Kee
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.72,0:01:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,成为五名被绑架书商中第四位重返香港的人\N{\fs(20)}became the fourth of five booksellers to resurface in Hong Kong
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.64,0:01:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他的故事传遍全球\N{\fs(20)}His story spread around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,2015年10月（解说误为2016）林荣基\N{\fs(20)}In October 2015 Lam Wing Kee
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,铜锣湾书店店长 在深圳失踪\N{\fs(20)}a book seller in Hong Kong disappeared in the South of China
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他的家人8个月没有他的任何消息\N{\fs(20)}For eight months his relatives had no news of him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.86,0:02:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,恢复自由后 他开了一个记者会\N{\fs(20)}Upon his release he gave a press conference
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.14,0:02:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,讲述了他被中国政府绑架和拘押的经历\N{\fs(20)}where he said he was kidnapped and detained by Chinese authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.30,0:02:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我非常害怕\N{\fs(20)}I was really scared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.46,0:02:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道在哪里 也没有人可以求助\N{\fs(20)}I was lost I felt lonely with no one to help me 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.18,0:02:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道他们要干什么\N{\fs(20)}I didn't know what they do to me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.60,0:02:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他们做的是非法的\N{\fs(20)}What they did was not legal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.34,0:02:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道他们是否会正式起诉我\N{\fs(20)}I wondered if they would have put me on trial
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.40,0:02:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,失踪事件过去两年 林荣基仍无法释怀\N{\fs(20)}Two years after his disappearance Lam Wing Kee still can't turn the page
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.10,0:02:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,书店已被当局下令停业\N{\fs(20)}The bookstore in which he worked was closed by order of the authortities
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的书店\N{\fs(20)}Here is my bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.54,0:02:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,当我到附近\N{\fs(20)}When I come in to the neigborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.18,0:02:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,就过来看一下\N{\fs(20)}I came here to take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.28,0:02:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,最近贴了一张通知\N{\fs(20)}Someone recently put a note
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.08,0:02:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,上面写着暂停营业\N{\fs(20)}There it says hold on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:03:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,一些老客户非常喜欢我们的书店\N{\fs(20)}Some customers were really grateful for the work that was done in this bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,林荣基不是个案\N{\fs(20)}Lam Wing Kee isn't the only one who went missing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,人权律师王宇失踪了18个月\N{\fs(20)}Wang Yu a human rights lawyer went missing for eighteen month
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.06,0:03:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞典一个非政府组织负责人彼得·达林失踪了23天\N{\fs(20)}Peter Dahlin the Swedish head of an NGO wasn't seen for 23 days
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.08,0:03:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,李文足仍在寻找她失踪的丈夫\N{\fs(20)}Li Wenzu is still looking for her husband
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.32,0:03:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,类似还有几百人被绑架 完全失去和外面世界的联系\N{\fs(20)}Like them hundreds of others have been kidnapped and hidden away from the outside world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他们经受到了什么\N{\fs(20)}What happens when these people vanish
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.90,0:03:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他们被关在哪里\N{\fs(20)}Where are they detained
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.46,0:03:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,为何人权卫士们受到如此密集的打击\N{\fs(20)}Why are the targets so often defenders of human rights
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们采访了几位被失踪的当事人\N{\fs(20)}We track down some of China's disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:03:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,王宇是中国知名的人权律师\N{\fs(20)}Wang Yu is one of China's most famous human rights lawyers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.84,0:04:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,也是首批被失踪的人\N{\fs(20)}and was among the first to disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,顶着自身和家人安全的压力 她秘密接受了我们的采访\N{\fs(20)}She agrees to meet us in secret dispite threats to her and her family
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.92,0:04:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,2015年七月九日深夜 她在家中被国安人员带走\N{\fs(20)}On July 9th 2015 in the middle of the night she was arrested at home by the state security services
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.20,0:04:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,冲进来很多人 几十个\N{\fs(20)}There were a lot of them several dozen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把我按在床上 把这个手反背过来\N{\fs(20)}They throw me on the bed put my hands behind my back
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人压过来 然后压过来以后\N{\fs(20)}There were a lot of them against me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.06,0:04:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,就把我拷上手铐\N{\fs(20)}They handcuffed me and held me tight
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.90,0:04:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,戴上黑头套\N{\fs(20)}Then they put a bag over my head
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就给我往门外拖\N{\fs(20)}and they took me out of my home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,王宇被控颠覆国家政权\N{\fs(20)}Wang Yu was accused of subverting state power
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,被关押 被酷刑\N{\fs(20)}For more than a year she was detained and tortured
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,很长时间不让吃饭 不让喝水\N{\fs(20)}They deprived me of food and water sleep too
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.40,0:04:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,然后五天五夜不让睡觉\N{\fs(20)}They prevented me from sleeping for five days and five nights
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:05:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉他们的目的是把我虐待死一样\N{\fs(20)}I felt they wanted to torture me until I died
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.64,0:05:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道当时是怎么过过来的\N{\fs(20)}I still wonder how I made it to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,好像是死了一次了\N{\fs(20)}In fact I felt as though I died there
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,从王宇突然失踪那晚起 当局开始全面打压异议人士\N{\fs(20)}The sudden disappearance of Wang Yu marked the beginning of a wave of arrest in China
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.66,0:05:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,涉及了将近300名律师和人权捍卫者\N{\fs(20)}In total nearly three hundred laywers and human rights defenders disappeared from one day to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人被判有期徒刑\N{\fs(20)}Some have since been sentenced to long jail terms
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,因为打压从2015年7月9日开始 被称为709事件\N{\fs(20)}The purge which started on the 9th of July 2015 has become known as the 709 inccident
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在北京我们有幸走访到一位还在为被打压同行进行辩护的律师\N{\fs(20)}In Beijing we met one of the only lawyers to defend his colleges who's been imprisoned or threated by the Chinese authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.12,0:05:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他的办公室有几十个这样的案卷\N{\fs(20)}In his office he has dozens of files
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,梁小军(人权律师) 很多涉案人员及家属和我签了委托书 这样我可以代理他们\N{\fs(20)}There are many relatives of the members of the 709 inccident who have filed their cases with us so that I can represent them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,有很多 很多委托书\N{\fs(20)}I can show you their letters there are many
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.24,0:06:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,比如这些人的 像这个是李玉凤的\N{\fs(20)}For example here there is a letter from Li Yufeng
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.08,0:06:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,涉嫌寻讯滋事\N{\fs(20)}She was accused of disturbing public order
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.26,0:06:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,已经被抓了\N{\fs(20)}she was arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这是江天勇的委托书 当时江天勇害怕自己被抓\N{\fs(20)}This is a letter from Jiang Tianyong he was afraid of being arrested 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,梁小军知道接这些敏感案件 他也可能被失踪\N{\fs(20)}Liang Xiaojun knows that by taking these cases he could also disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我也害怕也有恐惧\N{\fs(20)}I am scared too of course I am scared
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得作为人权案件的代理律师 很多人都生活在恐惧之中\N{\fs(20)}I think that many human rights lawyers live in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,2012年生效的一条法律允许当局带走嫌疑犯\N{\fs(20)}Since 2012 a Chinese law allows authorities to remove suspects and hold them in secret
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:07:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,并秘密关押长达6个月的时间\N{\fs(20)}This detention can last six months
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这样的法律条文 梁小军更愿意称其为黑监狱\N{\fs(20)}A legal framework for what Liang Xiaojun prefers to call Black Jails
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.84,0:07:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在中国它不叫黑监狱 叫指定居所监视居住\N{\fs(20)}In China the Black Jails we call them Residential Surveillance at a Disignated Place
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他说这个地方是我指定的地方\N{\fs(20)}Can be anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,对你进行监视居住 实际上就是失踪\N{\fs(20)}In fact that says these people has been disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,具体在哪里我们并不知道\N{\fs(20)}It's not clear where these places are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.48,0:07:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,出来的人他们也不能具体指明在哪里\N{\fs(20)}Even the people who come out can't say where they were
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他们被带到那个地方以后 进一个小黑屋 见不到阳光 然后里面有人进行24小时看守\N{\fs(20)}Inside these people are placed in a room where guards monitor them 24x7
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,全程记录\N{\fs(20)}And everything they do was recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.44,0:07:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,限制身体活动\N{\fs(20)}Their movements are limited
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,对他们进行殴打 甚至酷刑\N{\fs(20)}They are beaten tortured
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.48,0:07:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,对他们询问\N{\fs(20)}They must answer questions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.26,0:07:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至进行心理折磨\N{\fs(20)}They are tortured physically and psychologically
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这种地方你说不是监狱 但实际上它就是黑监狱\N{\fs(20)}These places aren't called Black Jails but in fact they are Black Jails
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这些失踪行为是由中国政府协调操控的\N{\fs(20)}These disappearances are orchestrated by the Chinese government
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,在习近平掌握最高权力以后 开始了对公民社会和不同意见的全面打压\N{\fs(20)}Since taking office Xi Jinping has been cracking down on civil society and surpressing all dissenting voices
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,坚决反对一切削弱 歪曲 否定党的领导和我国社会主义制度的言行\N{\fs(20)}We must firmly fight the words and actions that undermine and disrupt the authority of the parties
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.80,0:08:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个对希望拥有更多自由的人的警告\N{\fs(20)}A warning for anyone who wants more freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,对国际人权组织来说 这次打压让人联想起中国历史的几次黑暗时期\N{\fs(20)}For human rights groups this repression is reminicent of dark times in Chinese history
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.36,0:08:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,大赦国际中国研究员威廉： 1978年以来中国调整路线开始改革开放 尽力融入国际社会\N{\fs(20)}Since reform and opening in 1978 when China took a historic change of course to try to reintegrate with the world and with global institutions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.10,0:09:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这次打压可以说是自89天安门事件以来最严重的一次\N{\fs(20)}Its been one of the worst crackdowns since arguably since the Tiananmen Square crackdown in 1989
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,在中国 有一位律师成为北京政府威权倾向的代表性人物\N{\fs(20)}In China one lawyer has become the symbol of Beijing's authoritarian tendencies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.86,0:09:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,王全璋是数百名失踪人员中唯一一位至今没有任何下落的人\N{\fs(20)}Wang Quanzhuang is the last of the hundreds missing people never to have resurfaced
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.26,0:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,李文足（王全璋妻子） 这是15年5月我们一起的相片 \N{\fs(20)}This photo was taken in May 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.14,0:09:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,就隔了两个月 他就被抓了\N{\fs(20)}Two months later he was arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这张相片基本上记住了我们最后在一起相处的时间吧\N{\fs(20)}This is one of the last beautiful moments we have together
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.80,0:09:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他2年半前失踪以后\N{\fs(20)}Since his disappearance two and a half years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.90,0:09:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他妻子和现在已经5岁的儿子再也没有得到过他的消息\N{\fs(20)}his wife and their 5 year old son haven't heard from him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,想爸爸\N{\fs(20)}I miss my dad
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,贴到这儿吧\N{\fs(20)}Here I put this picture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.54,0:10:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸快回来 爸爸快回来\N{\fs(20)}There it says Dad come back quickly Dad come back quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,王全璋被带走后有一直被秘密关押\N{\fs(20)}Since his arrest Wang Quanzhuang has been held in secret
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.50,0:10:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,没人知道他的下落\N{\fs(20)}Nobody knows where he is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.02,0:10:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,律师 我聘请的律师从来没有被会见过\N{\fs(20)}The lawyers I hired to defend him don't have the right to visit him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,包括这个通讯我们没有\N{\fs(20)}And I don't have the right to communiate with him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没有他的一点点消息\N{\fs(20)}We don't have any news 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道在里面是怎么样\N{\fs(20)}I don't know how he is doing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.82,0:10:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道他这个人是不是还 我没办法去想 不知道 \N{\fs(20)}in fact I don't even know if he is still alive but I don't allow myself to think about that because it's too painful to imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,没有他任何消息\N{\fs(20)}I don't know anything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样被中国政府 就是这样\N{\fs(20)}I have no news
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.64,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,把一个人就这样 一个好人 就因为说了真话 是律师 平白无故消失了\N{\fs(20)}My husband was such a beautiful person and honest man
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,890多天了 两年半 没有他任何消息\N{\fs(20)}Because of the Chinese government its been 890 days two and half years now that I have no news
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们对中国政府方面提出了有关王全璋下落的采访要求 但没有收到答复\N{\fs(20)}The Chinese authorities didn't respond to our request for interviews regarding Wang Quanzhuang's fate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在中国 捍卫自由会导致流亡\N{\fs(20)}In China defending freedom can lead to exile
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,邻国泰国成了流亡人士的避难港\N{\fs(20)}A neighboring country has become a refuge for those fleeing repression
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是几百名流亡中国公民的藏身地\N{\fs(20)}We traval to Tailand where hundreds of Chinese nationals are hiding out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.58,0:11:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,也是瑞典活动家彼得用于避难的新家\N{\fs(20)}It's also home now to a Swedish activist who sought refuge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.82,0:11:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得·达林曾是北京一个帮助中国人权捍卫者组织的负责人\N{\fs(20)}Peter Dahlin used to head up an NGO in Beijing helping human rights defenders
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.90,0:11:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,当局在2016年1月将他逮捕 指控他颠覆政权\N{\fs(20)}For this the Chinese government accused him of subversion and arrested him in January 2016
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.28,0:11:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在一本由十多位被失踪者在海外出版的新书中 他也讲述了他的故事\N{\fs(20)}He's told the story of his disapperance and detention in a book written with other victims
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,有十一个律师 媒体人 非政府组织员工参与了这本书\N{\fs(20)}We got eleven people lawyers some media workers NGO workers 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.66,0:12:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们都被指定居所监视居住\N{\fs(20)}All were placed in RSDP -- the Black Jails of Chinese power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.50,0:12:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得好几天不让睡觉\N{\fs(20)}Peter Dahlin was deprived of sleep for several days
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.56,0:12:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里你被隔离\N{\fs(20)}Because in here you are alone there is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.94,0:12:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,没有检察官来看你\N{\fs(20)}There is no prosecuter that will come to shake on you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,没有律师会见\N{\fs(20)}There is no right to access a lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,家人不知道你的关押地点\N{\fs(20)}Your family will not be notified where you are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要任何司法程序他们可以关你6个月\N{\fs(20)}And they can keep you for six months without any judicial process
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.14,0:12:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有上诉的权力\N{\fs(20)}You have no right to any appeal
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.98,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,彼得被关押23天\N{\fs(20)}Peter Dahlin remained locked up for 23 days
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,为了得到自由 他被迫在电视上公开认罪\N{\fs(20)}To get out he was forced to confess his crimes on a Chinese public television
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我的行为违反了中国的法律\N{\fs(20)}I violated the Chinese law through my activities here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.66,0:12:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我伤害了中国政府\N{\fs(20)}and I have caused harm to the Chinese government
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.70,0:12:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我也伤害了中国人民的感情\N{\fs(20)}and I have hurt the feelings of the Chinese people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.52,0:12:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我真诚地道歉\N{\fs(20)}I apologize sincerely for this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.40,0:12:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,对于这些我感到非常抱歉\N{\fs(20)}and I am very sorry for what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的内容都事先安排好\N{\fs(20)}Everything that has been said was written down before
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.02,0:13:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,问什么如何回答都有严格审查好的书面文稿\N{\fs(20)}The questions and the answers were written down studied adjusted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,其实就是我和央视的记者\N{\fs(20)}And it was basically me and this journalist from CCTV
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,都有我们的稿子 她有稿子 我也有 她读她的 我读我的\N{\fs(20)}who would simply read our lines she had the paper I had the paper she would read the question I would read the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,近年来中国加大了强迫认罪的使用\N{\fs(20)}In recent years China has increased the use of forced confessions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.92,0:13:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,强迫认罪被作为证据用于庭审 这也可以减弱人权捍卫者的威望\N{\fs(20)}They are used as evidence during trials and undermines the power of human rights defenders
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,大赦国际中国研究员威廉： 当你看到你熟识的人权捍卫者\N{\fs(20)}When you look at someone that you've respected and you know that they are fighters for human rights
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在说一些你绝对想不到他们会说的话的时候\N{\fs(20)}Then you see them reading a statement and saying something that you will never believe that they would say before
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.32,0:13:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这会让人们害怕\N{\fs(20)}I mean that stikes fear inside people
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,难以想象政府做了什么才会使他们说那样的话\N{\fs(20)}because they only can imagine what the government did in order to get that person to say those type of things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.44,0:13:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,为了避免这样的情况 杨伯军（音）在两年前决定离开北京\N{\fs(20)}To avoid such a scenario Yang Bojun decided to leave Beijing two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.22,0:14:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在曼谷的街头见到了他\N{\fs(20)}We catch up with him in the streets of Bangkok
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.90,0:14:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他在中国是大学的经济学老师 同时推动中国民主化\N{\fs(20)}In China he taught economics at university and was active in the prodemocracy movement
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,中国的政府大力抓捕我们这种不同政见者\N{\fs(20)}The Chinese communist party wants to arrent people like me who have different political opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.56,0:14:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,为了不坐牢不受迫害我别无选择\N{\fs(20)}To avoid prison and to void being prosecuted I have no other choice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.62,0:14:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,没有办法才逃到这里来生活\N{\fs(20)}I can only run away and live here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在曼谷也比较危险\N{\fs(20)}Even here in Bangkok there are always risks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.42,0:14:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,为了避免麻烦我常常会看看有没有人跟踪我 出来的时候\N{\fs(20)}To avoid to put myself in danger I often look behind me to make sure I am not being followed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.64,0:14:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,即使离开中国 杨伯军（音）也没有安全感\N{\fs(20)}Even outside of China Yang Bojun doesn't feel safe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,北京政府常常跨出国门抓捕异见者\N{\fs(20)}Beijing doesn't let borders limits its persuit of dissidents
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他远离家人藏到一个诊所里\N{\fs(20)}Today he is forced to hide far from his family in the premises of a medical office
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.52,0:14:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我起居的地方\N{\fs(20)}Here is where I live
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:15:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我在里面生活 睡觉 做饭\N{\fs(20)}This is where I sleep I cook everything happens here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.42,0:15:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这是洗衣机 就在这个地方\N{\fs(20)}It's also here that I run my machines
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.34,0:15:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前是在北京买了一个二居室\N{\fs(20)}Before I owned my apartment in China a two bed room apartment with a living room too 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.32,0:15:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,和爱人孩子我们三个人住在一起\N{\fs(20)}I lived here with my wife and child
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.38,0:15:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在泰国杨伯军（音）取得了联合国难民身份\N{\fs(20)}In Tailand Yang Bojun has been granted refugee status by the United Nations
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就觉得很不可思议 自己从来没想到会流亡泰国\N{\fs(20)}To me this is an incredible situation because in China I would never have imagined that one day I would be exiled in Tailand
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.70,0:15:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,成为难民\N{\fs(20)}and that I would become a refugee
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.94,0:15:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,不过是想为这个国家 为了让人民生活得好点\N{\fs(20)}All that I did was to improve my country and to serve the people
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,没想到自己因此流亡海外\N{\fs(20)}I didn't think it would lead to me being in exile
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.92,0:15:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,逃到国外 用古人的话来说\N{\fs(20)}I would have to flee and live abroad
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,变成鬼了 做梦也没有想到这个事情是这样一个情况\N{\fs(20)}I didn't think I would be like a ghost for my country even in my worst nightmares I wouldn't think I would get here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.10,0:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,家人 朋友 祖国 杨伯军（音）都失去了\N{\fs(20)}His family his friends his country for Yang Bojun the Chinese government has taken them all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.54,0:16:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,泰国也只是第一站\N{\fs(20)}And Tailand is only an initial step
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他希望能在美国重建自己的人生\N{\fs(20)}He hopes to rebuild his life in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,希望能顺利离开 而不是被失踪\N{\fs(20)}escaping again rather than disappearing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,本台记者Forget和Vedeilhe\N{\fs(20)}By Angelique Forget and Antoine Vedeilhe
